For this circuit you will need a motor, transistor, 330R resistor and a red breadboard wire.
Insert your MicroView and Programmer with Pin 1 in hole C9.
Select your motor and insert the red wire into hole C17 your breadboard.

Insert the motors black wire into hole
C18 of your breadboard.
Select your transistor and insert it as shown into pins A15-A17 of your breadboard.
Select your 330R resistor and insert it as shown into pins B12 and B16 of your breadboard.
Swipe Left to go to the next page
Swipe Right to go back to the previous page
If you have a keyboard you can also use the arrow keys
